Also, remember the lesson about Liquidity – move from Discount to Premium and vice versa is a run in Internal Liquidity, once price breaks either the Dealing Range High or the Dealing Range Low, it enters the External Liquidity.

results.signature: IF Dealing Range defined AND HTF Bias = BEARISH THEN Premium Zone = 50%-100% of range (seek for shorts) AND Discount Zone = 0%-50% of range (avoid for shorts)
results.source_quote: the highest probability short positions happen in the Premium side of the Dealing Range

results.signature: IF Bullish FVG exists AND FVG is in Discount Zone THEN FVG Confirmed for Long entry

results.signature: IF Short position in profit THEN TP1 = nearest internal sell-side liquidity

results.signature: IF Long position in profit THEN TP1 = nearest internal buy-side liquidity

results.signature: IF partial at TP1 taken THEN Runner Target = external liquidity
results.source_quote: Also, in some cases, leaving a portion of the position running if the trade is with the Higher TF order flow for price to break out and seek for some external liquidity levels.

results.signature: IF EURUSD forms a higher low when DXY forms a higher high (SMT Divergence) THEN expect a reversal
results.source_quote: when DXY forms a higher high but EURUSD fails to expand lower and form a lower low and instead forms a higher low, this is a crack in correlation – SMT Divergence. That’s when we expect a reversal to happen

results.signature: IF EURUSD forms a lower low when DXY fails to form a higher high (SMT Divergence) THEN expect a reversal
results.source_quote: When EURUSD ran the SSLQ and formed a lower low, DXY failed to run the BSLQ and instead of forming a higher high, formed a lower high. Then as you could’ve guessed, the overall picture changes drastically.

results.signature: IF EURUSD runs BSLQ THEN potential bullish expansion
results.source_quote: After a sharp expansion lower price on DXY runs SSLQ, EURUSD gives a sharp expansion higher and runs BSLQ.

results.signature: IF EURUSD runs SSLQ THEN potential bearish expansion
results.source_quote: After a sharp expansion lower price on DXY runs SSLQ, EURUSD gives a sharp expansion higher and runs BSLQ.

results.signature: IF price trades above prior swing high (buy-side liquidity) AND then reverses back below that high THEN Bullish Liquidity Sweep = TRUE
results.source_quote: Price expanded to the higher to take out buy stops, why? Because they (the Informed Money), will want to sell at a higher price, take the Liquidity and cover their long positions that they opened to run the price higher.

results.signature: IF price trades below prior swing low (sell-side liquidity) AND then reverses back above that low THEN Bearish Liquidity Sweep = TRUE
results.source_quote: What retail sees as a “double bottom” area as strong support, what we see is all the sell stops resting below (retail stop losses) – that’s our target and a magnet where the price will be drawn to.
